name: CardiopulmonaryResuscitationI9
title: Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation I9
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains procedures for cardiopulmonary resuscitation most commonly used for patients.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have a procedure performed for cardiopulmonary resuscitation. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the  "Procedure" category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Codes representing the ICD-9 code system for the procedure of cardiopulmonary resuscitation.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet inclusion criteria.)
